d%20to%20be%20lower%20in%20Texas%2C%20California%20has%20Texas%20beat%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20property%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETexas%20has%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20property%20tax%20percentage%20rates%20in%20the%20country%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20property%20taxes%2C%20which%20are%20based%20on%20the%20value%20of%20a%20piece%20of%20property%2C%20represent%20the%20single%20largest%20source%20of%20state%20and%20local%20revenue.%20The%20money%20from%20property%20taxes%20typically%20helps%20fund%20local%20amenities%2C%20including%20schools%2C%20roads%2C%20and%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20has%20a%20proposition%20in%20place%2C%20known%20as%20Prop%2013%2C%20which%20keeps%20property%20taxes%20from%20exceeding%201%25%20of%20a%20home's%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20such%2C%20the%20effective%20property%20tax%20rate%20comes%20out%20to%20an%20average%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-property-taxes-every-us-state%2336-california-16%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E0.75%25%20in%20California%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20levies%20significantly%20higher%20property%20taxes%2C%20partly%20because%20it%20doesn't%20collect%20state%20personal%20income%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20property%20tax%20percentage%20rate%20in%20the%20state%20is%20among%20the%20highest%20in%20the%20nation%20at%201.74%25%2C%20according%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20past%20reporting.%20In%20her%20work%20as%20a%20realtor%2C%20Bailey%20said%20she%20typically%20sees%20property%20tax%20percentage%20rates%20in%20Texas%20sitting%20between%201.6%25%20to%202.7%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECharles%20Denson%2C%20a%20tax%20expert%20with%20Gill%2C%20Denson%20%26amp%3B%20Company%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20what%20a%20nearby%20home%20sells%20for%20can%20also%20affect%20how%20much%20property%20tax%20rates%20increase%20for%20homeowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20you%20weren't%20selling%20your%20house%2C%20your%20neighbors%20might%20have%20sold%20their%20house%20for%20a%20lot%20so%20your%20tax%20bill%20is%20going%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Denson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20Jennifer%20and%20Chuck%20Balek%20and%20their%20family%20in%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F646e919e63b4c50018c399d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJennifer%20and%20Chuck%20Balek%20moved%20their%20family%20from%20Camarillo%2C%20California%20to%20Rockwall%2C%20Texas%20in%20April%202021.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jennifer%20Balek.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20Texas%20property%20taxes%20are%20offset%20by%20other%20perks%20in%20the%20state%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Texas%20property%20rates%20may%20be%20off-putting%20for%20some%20considering%20a%20change%20of%20scenery%2C%20many%20who%20have%20actually%20made%20the%20move%20from%20California%20to%20Texas%20find%20the%20increased%20property%20taxes%20negligible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20a%20state%20income%20tax%20was%20something%20Chuck%20and%20Jennifer%20Balek%20took%20into%20consideration%20ahead%20of%20their%202021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fmoved-california-to-texas-will-never-go-back-expensive-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emove%20from%20Camarillo%2C%20California%2C%20to%20Rockwall%2C%20Texas.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTexas%20doesn't%20have%20a%20state%20income%20tax%20which%20was%20equivalent%20to%20like%20a%2010%25%20raise%20for%20both%20of%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Chuck%20Balek%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20people%20ask%20us%20about%20our%20property%20taxes%2C%20I%20say%20we're%20not%20really%20paying%20more%20than%20what%20we%20paid%20in%20California%2C%26quot%3B%20Jennifer%20B