ident%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20called%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20last%20Friday%2C%20he%20said%20he%20was%20hoping%20the%20US%20and%20UK%20would%20follow%20suit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Funqualified-support-of-israels-allies-over-gaza-is-no-longer-a-given-with-marked-shift-in-rhetoric-13008962%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Funqualified-support-of-israels-allies-over-gaza-is-no-longer-a-given-with-marked-shift-in-rhetoric-13008962%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Funqualified-support-of-israels-allies-over-gaza-is-no-longer-a-given-with-marked-shift-in-rhetoric-13008962%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Insufficient%20Progress%20in%20Limiting%20Temperature%20Rise%20and%20Tackling%20Climate%20Change%3A%20UN%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F12%2F28202110%2Frefinery.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Countries%E2%80%99%20plans%20to%20deal%20with%20climate%20change%20by%20limiting%20the%20global%20temperature%20rise%20to%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20and%20to%20meet%20the%20goals%20of%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20remain%20insufficient%2C%20as%20per%20a%20United%20Nations%20report%20released%20on%20Tuesday%20(November%2014).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20lot%20more%20action%20is%20needed%20now%20to%20decrease%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20carbon%20emissions%20and%20avoid%20the%20worst%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20it%20has%20warned.%20The%20report%20comes%20just%2015%20days%20before%20the%20UN%20Climate%20Change%20Conference%20(COP28)%20is%20scheduled%20to%20take%20place%20in%20Dubai.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENDC%20synthesis%20reports%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%202015%20Paris%20Agreement%20%E2%80%93%20which%20India%20is%20also%20signatory%20to%20%E2%80%93%20mandates%20that%20each%20party%20should%20prepare%2C%20communicate%20and%20maintain%20nationally%20determined%20contributions%20(NDCs)%20that%20it%20intends%20to%20achieve%20to%20adapt%20to%20and%20mitigate%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInformation%20on%20targets%2C%20policies%20and%20measures%20to%20reduce%20national%20emissions%20and%20adapt%20to%20climate%20change%20impacts%20are%20listed%20in%20annual%20%E2%80%98NDC%20synthesis%20reports%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20reports%20are%20released%20by%20the%20UN%20Framework%20Convention%20on%20Climate%20Change%20%E2%80%93%20which%20has%20been%20adopted%20by%20198%20parties%20including%20India%20%E2%80%93%20which%20aims%20to%20combat%20%E2%80%9Cdangerous%20human%20interference%20with%20the%20climate%20system%E2%80%9D.%20Its%20secretariat%20analyses%20and%20reviews%20the%20latest%20and%20available%20information%20on%20climate%20change%2C%20apart%20from%20conducting%20several%20exercises%20including%20maintaining%20a%20registry%20of%20every%20country%E2%80%99s%20NDCs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20February%202021%2C%20it%20released%20the%20first%20analysis%20of%20the%20member%20parties%E2%80%99%20NDCs%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20second%20last%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20year%2C%20the%20UN%20body%20analysed%20168%20NDCs%20of%20195%20parties%20signatory%20to%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%2C%20including%2020%20new%20or%20updated%20NDCs%20submitted%20up%20until%20September%2025%2C%202023.%20It%20projected%20emission%20levels%20resulting%20from%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20NDCs%20when%20compared%20to%20emission%20scenarios%20assessed%20by%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20(IPCC).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fg20-why-many-of-the-delhi-declarations-climate-commitments-are-vague%5C%22%3EG20%3A%20Why%20Many%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Declaration%E2%80%99s%20Climate%20Commitments%20Are%20Vague%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20parties%20(95%25)%20provided%20the%20information%20necessary%20for%20%E2%80%9Cclarity%2C%20transparency%20and%20understanding%20of%20their%20NDCs%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20report%20found.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAround%2080%25%20of%20the%20parties%20also%20provided%20information%20on%20adaptation%20strategies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20(97%25)%20also%20provided%20information%20on%20their%20NDC%20planning%20processes%20and%20%E2%80%9Creferred%20to%20their%20implementation%20plans%2C%20communicating%20information%20on%20their%20institutional%20arrangements%2C%20stakeholder%20engagement%20processes%20and%20policy%20instruments%2C%20including%20legislation%2C%20strategies%2C%20plans%20and%20policies%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMore%20than%2090%25%20of%20the%20parties%20identified%20energy%20supply%20as%20a%20specific%20priority%20area%20in%20their%20mitigation%20options%20to%20tackle%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20coal-fired%20power%20generation%20was%20the%20single%20largest%20source%20of%20energy-related%20CO%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Csub%3E%3Cspan%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fsub%3E%3Cspan%3E%20emissions%20globally%20in%202021%20(9.7%20gigatonnes%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20equivalent)%2C%20and%20that%20there%20were%20more%20than%208%2C000%20coal-fired%20power%20plants%20operating%20in%20roughly%2090%20countries%20providing%202%20million%20jobs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20only%209%25%20of%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20which%20together%20account%20for%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20the%20total%20global%20electricity%20generation%20from%20coal%20in%202021%20%E2%80%93%20listed%20measures%20such%20as%20replacing%20coal-fired%20power%20plants%20with%20less%20polluting%20alternatives.%20Again%2C%20only%204%25%20of%20parties%20mentioned%20the%20need%20for%20or%20measures%20required%20for%20a%20just%20transition%20for%20communities%20and%20workers%20dependent%20on%20coal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EActions%20not%20enough%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilar%20to%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20analysis%2C%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20report%20shows%20that%20while%20emissions%20are%20no%20longer%20increasing%20after%202030%20when%20compared%20to%202019%20levels%2C%20they%20are%20still%20not%20declining%20as%20rapidly%20as%20they%20should.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPer%20the%20report%2C%20even%20if%20the%20latest%20NDCs%20are%20implemented%2C%20they%20will%20still%20increase%20emissions%20by%20about%208.8%25%20when%20compared%20to%202010%20levels.%20This%2C%20the%20UN%20press%20release%20said%2C%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmarginal%20improvement%E2%80%9D%20over%20the%202022%20assessment%2C%20which%20found%20that%20countries%20were%20on%20a%20path%20to%20increase%20emissions%20by%2010.6%25%20by%202030%20compared%20to%202010%20levels.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F15195900%2Fglobal-warming_India_summer-heat-1024x679.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Global%20warming.%20Credit%3A%20Jorge%20Vasconez%2FUnsplash%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F15195900%2Fglobal-warming_India_summer-heat-1024x679.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F15195900%2Fglobal-warming_India_summer-heat-300x199.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F15195900%2Fglobal-warming_India_summer-heat-768x509.jpg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-249614%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22557%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EScientists%20have%20said%202023%20is%20on%20track%20to%20be%20the%20warmest%20year%20on%20record%2C%20around%201.4%20%C2%B0C%20above%20pre-industrial%20average%20temperatures.%20Credit%3A%20Jorge%20Vasconez%2FUnsplash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%202030%2C%20emissions%20are%20projected%20to%20be%202%25%20below%202019%20levels%2C%20highlighting%20that%20the%20peaking%20of%20global%20emissions%20will%20occur%20within%20this%20decade.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20order%20to%20achieve%20the%20peaking%20of%20emissions%20before%202030%2C%20the%20report%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20conditional%20elements%20of%20the%20NDCs%20need%20to%20be%20implemented%2C%20which%20depends%20mostly%20on%20access%20to%20enhanced%20financial%20resources%2C%20technology%20transfer%20and%20technical%20cooperation%2C%20and%20capacity-building%20support%3B%20as%20well%20as%20the%20availability%20of%20market-based%20mechanisms.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20latest%20science%20from%20the%20IPCC%20indicates%20that%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20need%20to%20be%20cut%20by%2043%25%20by%202030%2C%20compared%20to%202019%20levels%2C%20to%20limit%20temperature%20rise%20to%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20century%20and%20avoid%20the%20worst%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CToday%E2%80%99s%20report%20shows%20that%20governments%20combined%20are%20taking%20baby%20steps%20to%20avert%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20And%20it%20shows%20why%20governments%20must%20make%20bold%20strides%20forward%20at%20COP28%20in%20Dubai%2C%20to%20get%20on%20track%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20executive-secretary%20of%20UN%20Climate%20Change%2C%20Simon%20Stiell.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20means%20COP28%20must%20be%20a%20clear%20turning%20point.%20Governments%20must%20not%20only%20agree%20what%20stronger%20climate%20actions%20will%20be%20taken%20but%20also%20start%20showing%20exactly%20how%20to%20deliver%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNDCs%20remain%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20our%20shared%20vision%20of%20achieving%20the%20Paris%20targets%2C%20including%20keeping%20the%20target%20of%20below%202%20degrees%20and%20aspiring%20to%20limiting%20%5Bthe%5D%20increase%20to%20below%201.5%20degrees%2C%E2%80%9D%20COP27%20president%20and%20Egypt%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20minister%20Sameh%20Shoukry%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Sharm%20El-Sheikh%20leaders%20discussed%20several%20initiatives%20to%20assist%20us%20to%20reach%20that%20goal%2C%20as%20well%20as%20assist%20the%20Global%20South%20in%20adapting%20their%20economies%20accordingly.%20We%20need%20to%20keep%20the%20momentum%20going%20as%20there%20is%20no%20time%20to%20waste%20or%20lose%20focus%20on%20the%20target.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fwhat-is-cop-and-why-should-i-care%5C%22%3EWhat%20Is%20COP%20and%20Why%20Should%20I%20Care%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELong-term%20low-emission%20development%20strategies%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20second%20UN%20Climate%20Change%20report%20on%20long-term%20low-emission%20development%20strategies%2C%20also%20released%20on%20November%2014%2C%20looked%20at%20countries%E2%80%99%20plans%20to%20transition%20to%20net-zero%20emissions%20by%20or%20around%20mid-century.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%2C%20per%20a%20press%20release%2C%20indicated%20that%20these%20countries%E2%80%99%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20could%20be%20roughly%2063%25%20lower%20in%202050%20than%20in%202019%2C%20if%20all%20the%20long-term%20strategies%20are%20fully%20implemented%20on%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrent%20long-term%20strategies%20(representing%2075%20parties%20to%20the%20Paris%20Agreement)%20account%20for%2087%25%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20GDP%2C%2068%25%20of%20the%20global%20population%20in%202019%20and%20around%2077%25%20of%20global%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20in%202019%2C%20per%20the%20report.%20This%20is%20a%20strong%20signal%20that%20the%20world%20is%20starting%20to%20aim%20for%20net-zero%20emissions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20notes%2C%20however%2C%20that%20many%20net-zero%20targets%20remain%20uncertain%20and%20postpone%20into%20the%20future%20critical%20action%20that%20needs%20to%20take%20place%20immediately.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700063145000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F12%2F28202110%2Frefinery.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Finsufficient-progress-in-limiting-temperature-rise-and-tackling-climate-change-says-un-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%2C%20which%20was%20released%20on%20November%2014%2C%20shows%20that%20while%20emissions%20are%20no%20longer%20increasing%20after%202030%20when%20compared%20to%202019%20levels%2C%20they%20are%20still%20not%20declining%20as%20rapidly%20as%20they%20should.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Finsufficient-progress-in-limiting-temperature-rise-and-tackling-climate-change-says-un-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20%E2%80%98Interest%20of%20Gender%20Neutrality%E2%80%99%2C%20Parl%20Panel%20Recommends%20Keeping%20Section%20377%2C%20Criminalising%20Adultery%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F27110211%2FScreenshot-2023-05-27-at-11.00.50-AM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs%20that%20was%20tasked%20to%20examine%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-three-criminal-law-bills-using-criminal-law-to-establish-permanent-extra-constitutional-emergency-powers%5C%22%3E%20three%20new%20criminal%20Bills%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20recommended%20that%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20gender%20neutral%20laws%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%20which%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%2C%20should%20include%20the%20criminalisation%20of%20adultery%20and%20retain%20Section%20377.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Adhiniyam%20Bill%20(to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872)%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%20(to%20replace%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%2C%201973)%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsedition-law-repealed-three-new-bills-tabled-in-parliament-to-replace-criminal-laws%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20parliament%20on%20August%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bills%20were%20then%20referred%20to%20the%2031-member%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%2C%20headed%20by%20BJP%20MP%20Brij%20Lal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-adopts-reports-on-three-criminal-bills-several-dissent-notes-from-opposition%5C%22%3Eadopted%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20report%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20analyses%20the%20main%20recommendations%20and%20observations%20of%20the%20committee%20on%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20MPs%20had%20written%20in%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcriminal-bills-opposition-mp-dissent-note-hindi-imposition-copy-paste%5C%22%3Edissent%20notes%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20new%20legislations%20are%20%E2%80%9Clargely%20a%20copy-paste%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20existing%20laws.%20They%20had%20also%20opposed%20their%20Hindi%20names%2C%20flagged%20the%20lack%20of%20consultation%20and%20the%20diversity%20of%20domain%20expert%20opinion%2C%20and%20questioned%20the%20%E2%80%9Chaste%E2%80%9D%20in%20which%20the%20legislations%20are%20being%20introduced.%20Despite%20these%20objections%2C%20the%20committee%20report%20has%20hailed%20the%20new%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcriminal-bills-opposition-mp-dissent-note-hindi-imposition-copy-paste%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Copy%20Paste%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Hindi%20Imposition%E2%80%99%3A%20What%20Opposition%20MPs%E2%80%99%20Dissent%20Notes%20on%20the%20Criminal%20Bills%20Say%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERetain%20Section%20377%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20said%20that%20while%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202018%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-scraps-section-377-majoritarian-views-cannot-dictate-rights-says-cji%5C%22%3Eruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ENavtej%20Singh%20Johar%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%20that%20Section%20377%20of%20the%20IPC%20is%20in%20violation%20of%20Articles%2014%2C%2015%2C%2019%2C%20and%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20the%20law%20remained%20applicable%20in%20cases%20of%20non-consensual%20carnal%20intercourse%20with%20adults%2C%20all%20acts%20of%20carnal%20intercourse%20with%20minors%2C%20and%20acts%20of%20bestiality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20no%20such%20provision%20for%20non-consensual%20sexual%20offences%20against%20males%2C%20females%20and%20transgenders%20and%20for%20bestiality%20has%20been%20made%20in%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20(BNS)%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20feels%20that%20to%20align%20with%20the%20objectives%20stated%20in%20the%20BNS%E2%80%99s%20Statement%20of%20Objects%20and%20Reasons%2C%20which%20inter%20alia%20highlights%20the%20move%20towards%20gender-neutral%20offences%2C%20it%20is%20mandatory%20to%20reintroduce%20and%20retain%20Section%20377%20of%20the%20IPC.%20The%20Committee%2C%20therefore%2C%20recommends%20the%20government%20to%20include%20Section%20377%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20in%20the%20proposed%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERetain%20adultery%20as%20a%20gender-neutral%20criminal%20offence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20also%20cited%20the%20interests%20of%20gender%20neutrality%20in%20recommending%20that%20Section%20497%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20which%20was%20struck%20down%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202018%2C%20should%20be%20retained%20in%20the%20proposed%20legislation%20by%20%E2%80%9Cmaking%20it%20gender-neutral%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Section%20497%2C%20a%20person%20who%20had%20sexual%20intercourse%20with%20a%20married%20woman%20without%20the%20consent%20or%20connivance%20of%20her%20husband%20would%20be%20guilty%20of%20adultery.%20This%20was%20punishable%20with%20imprisonment%20or%20fine%20or%20both%3B%20but%20the%20woman%20was%20not%20punishable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fshould-adultery-be-a-crime-at-all%5C%22%3EShould%20Adultery%20Be%20a%20Crime%20at%20All%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20while%20striking%20down%20the%20law%20had%20said%20it%20was%20archaic%2C%20arbitrary%2C%20and%20paternalistic%20and%20that%20it%20infringed%20upon%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20autonomy%2C%20dignity%2C%20and%20privacy%2C%20and%20that%20it%20reduced%20the%20married%20woman%20to%20being%20her%20husband%E2%80%99s%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20regard%2C%20the%20committee%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage%20is%20considered%20sacred%20in%20Indian%20society%20and%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20safeguard%20its%20sanctity.%20For%20the%20sake%20of%20protecting%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage%2C%20this%20section%20should%20be%20retained%20in%20the%20Sanhita%20by%20making%20it%20gender-neutral%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeath%20penalty%20and%20Hindi%20imposition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20opposition%20MPs%20in%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcriminal-bills-opposition-mp-dissent-note-hindi-imposition-copy-paste%5C%22%3Edissent%20notes%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20highlighted%20the%20need%20to%20abolish%20the%20death%20penalty%20and%20wrote%20against%20the%20Hindi%20names%20of%20the%20three%20laws%2C%20the%20committee%20has%20not%20recommended%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20committee%20had%20considered%20the%20submissions%20on%20doing%20away%20with%20the%20death%20penalty%2C%20but%20left%20the%20matter%20to%20be%20decided%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%2C%20after%20considering%20the%20submissions%20regarding%20the%20death%20penalty%2C%20has%20understood%20that%20the%20reason%20for%20a%20passionate%20argument%20against%20death%20penalty%20is%20that%20the%20judicial%20system%20can%20be%20fallible%20and%20to%20prevent%20an%20innocent%20person%20from%20being%20wrongly%20sentenced%20to%20death.%20In%20this%20regard%2C%20the%20committee%20recommends%20that%20the%20matter%20may%20be%20left%20for%20the%20government%20to%20consider%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20said%20that%20the%20committee%20was%20satisfied%20with%20the%20arguments%20of%20the%20home%20ministry%20and%20that%20the%20Hindi%20names%20of%20the%20Bills%20are%20not%20a%20violation%20of%20Article%20348%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20which%20says%20that%20language%20to%20be%20used%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20in%20the%20high%20courts%2C%20as%20well%20as%20for%20Acts%2C%20Bills%20and%20other%20legal%20documents%2C%20shall%20be%20in%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FnpHbecvfc9o%3Fsi%3DeGrjjOE1jn1JXMtC%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20finds%20that%20as%20the%20text%20of%20the%20Sanhita%20is%20in%20English%2C%20it%20does%20not%20violate%20the%20provisions%20of%20Article%20348%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20The%20Committee%20is%20satisfied%20with%20the%20response%20of%20the%20Ministry%20and%20holds%20that%20the%20name%20given%20to%20the%20proposed%20legislation%20is%20not%20in%20violation%20of%20Article%20348%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDefining%20community%20service%2C%20life%20imprisonment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20recommended%20that%20while%20the%20new%20law%20proposes%20to%20change%20the%20definition%20of%20imprisonment%20for%20life%20to%20mean%20it%20as%20imprisonment%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20natural%20life%2C%20the%20courts%20have%20interpreted%20imprisonment%20for%20life%20simpliciter%20to%20mean%20a%20%E2%80%98whole%20life%20sentence%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20recommends%20that%20suitable%20amendments%20may%20be%20made%20in%20consultation%20with%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20and%20Justice%20to%20make%20clause%204(b)%20more%20comprehensive%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20also%20noted%20that%20while%20the%20introduction%20of%20community%20service%20is%20a%20welcome%20step%20and%20a%20reformatory%20approach%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cterm%20and%20nature%20of%20community%20service%E2%80%9D%20has%20not%20been%20specified%20and%20should%20be%20duly%20defined.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReplace%20mental%20illness%20with%20unsound%20mind%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20also%20recommended%20that%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98mental%20illness%E2%80%99%20be%20replaced%20with%20%E2%80%98unsound%20mind%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20the%20term%20mental%20illness%20is%20too%20wide%20in%20its%20import%20in%20comparison%20to%20unsound%20mind%2C%20as%20it%20appears%20to%20include%20even%20mood%20swings%20or%20voluntary%20intoxication%20within%20its%20ambit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20is%20also%20of%20the%20view%20that%20such%20a%20frivolous%20claim%2C%20if%20recognised%20as%20a%20valid%20defence%2C%20will%20spell%20doom%20for%20the%20prosecution%20as%20all%20defences%20will%20be%20claimed%20under%20this%20provision%2C%20thereby%20defeating%20the%20very%20purpose%20of%20this%20Sanhita%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERectify%20all%20grammatical%20and%20typographical%20errors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20noted%20typographical%20and%20grammatical%20errors%20in%20the%20text%20of%20the%20Bill%20that%20had%20also%20been%20raised%20by%20opposition%20MPs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20even%20a%20single%20typographical%20or%20grammatical%20error%20in%20the%20Sanhita%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20misinterpreted%20and%20diluting%20the%20intent%20of%20the%20provision.%20The%20committee%2C%20therefore%2C%20recommends%20the%20ministry%20to%20rectify%20such%20typographical%20and%20grammatical%20errors%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CRephrasing%E2%80%9D%20sedition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20claims%20in%20parliament%20that%20the%20sedition%20law%20has%20been%20deleted%2C%20opposition%20MPs%20had%20written%20in%20their%20dissent%20notes%20about%20reintroducing%20the%20law%20in%20a%20more%20draconian%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%2C%20however%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccomplimented%E2%80%9D%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20deleting%20the%20term%20and%20%E2%80%9Crephrasing%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20compliments%20the%20government%20in%20deleting%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98sedition%E2%80%99%20from%20criminal%20law%20by%20rephrasing%20it%20without%20compromising%20the%20security%20of%20the%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20finds%20it%20as%20a%20very%20progressive%20development.%20It%20is%20observed%20that%20in%20the%20Explanation%20part%20of%20clause%2C%20due%20to%20a%20typological%20error%20the%20sentence%20remains%20incomplete.%20The%20words%20%E2%80%98do%20not%20constitute%20offence%20under%20this%20section%E2%80%99%20may%20be%20added%20at%20the%20end.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECommittee%20hails%20%E2%80%9Cmilestone%20initiative%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20hailed%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cmilestone%20initiative%E2%80%9D%20in%20bringing%20these%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20opposition%20MPs%20had%20written%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20diversity%20in%20domain%20expert%20opinion%2C%20the%20committee%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20process%20of%20consultation%20undertaken%20has%20been%20exhaustive%20and%20comprehensive%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20comprehensive%20review%20of%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%20in%20our%20country%20was%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20to%20bring%20it%20on%20par%20with%20the%20contemporary%20aspirations%20of%20the%20people.%20Having%20taken%20a%20citizen-centric%20approach%2C%20these%20proposed%20laws%20serve%20as%20a%20reassurance%20to%20the%20Indian%20citizens.%20The%20committee%20feels%20that%20these%20Bills%20are%20much-awaited%20and%20much-needed%20reforms%20as%20well%20as%20an%20imperative%20for%20smooth%20and%20transparent%20functioning%20of%20our%20legal%20system%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700061324000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F27110211%2FScreenshot-2023-05-27-at-11.00.50-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-gender-neutrality-section-377-criminalising-adultery%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20in%20its%20report%20that%20was%20adopted%20last%20week%2C%20has%20given%20its%20recommendations%20for%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%20that%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-gender-neutrality-section-377-criminalising-adultery%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20The%20Who%E2%80%99s%20Who%20in%20the%20Data%20%7C%20Gorkan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15204207%2FScreenshot-2023-11-15-at-8.41.07%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBeyond%20politics%2C%20the%20Bihar%20caste%20survey%20is%20a%20revolutionary%20document.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20public%20document%2C%20the%20first%20ever%20after%201931%2C%20allowing%20for%20people%20to%20stand%20up%20and%20be%20counted.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20go%20down%20to%20the%20wire%2C%20on%20what%20each%20of%20the%20numbers%20unveiled%20mean.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWho%20are%20the%20people%20referred%20to%20by%20percentages%20in%20the%20survey%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EToday%20we%20look%20at%20Gorkan%20(0%20people)%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWere%20castes%20created%20before%20religion%3F%20Or%20was%20it%20religion%20that%20came%20first%3F%20This%20is%20not%20a%20very%20complicated%20question%20because%20occupations%20came%20into%20existence%20before%20either%20of%20them.%20A%20sense%20of%20community%20developed%20among%20humans%20as%20a%20result%20of%20their%20work.%20For%20example%2C%20agriculture%20is%20a%20social%20profession%20in%20which%20people%20of%20all%20castes%20are%20involved.%20No%20one%20can%20do%20farming%20alone.%20Initially%20agriculture%20was%20a%20profession%20adopted%20by%20everyone%20but%20segregation%20also%20took%20place%20on%20its%20basis.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20271px)%2085vw%2C%20271px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22271%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%20838w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-210x300.jpg%20210w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-715x1024.jpg%20715w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682410%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22388%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHere%2C%20we%20are%20not%20talking%20about%20the%20creation%20but%20the%20extinction%20of%20a%20caste.%20There%20are%20many%20castes%20mentioned%20in%20the%20report%20of%20the%20last%20public%20All%20India%20Caste%20Census%20conducted%20in%201931%20which%20no%20longer%20exist.%20At%20least%20they%20do%20not%20exist%20in%20Bihar%2C%20as%20revealed%20by%20the%20caste-based%20survey%20of%202022%20released%20by%20Bihar%20government.%20One%20of%20these%20castes%20groups%20is%20the%20Gorkan%20which%20is%20missing%20in%20the%20report%20of%20the%20Bihar%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20a%20caste%20which%20has%20exactly%20the%20same%20status%20in%20Islam%20as%20the%20Dom%20caste%20group%20does%20in%20Hinduism.%20The%20way%20the%20deceased%20in%20Hindu%20religion%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20%E2%80%98liberated%E2%80%99%20only%20through%20the%20fire%20ignited%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20someone%20belonging%20to%20the%20Dom%20caste%2C%20the%20dead%20in%20Islam%20are%20laid%20to%20rest%20owing%20to%20the%20labour%20of%20a%20Gorkan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEtymologically%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Egorkan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20Persian%20word%20where%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Egor%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20means%20grave%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20suffix%20for%20digger.%20Gorkan%20are%20gravediggers.%20The%20moment%20someone%20dies%2C%20a%20Gorkan%20is%20the%20first%20to%20be%20informed.%20He%20digs%20the%20grave%20at%20the%20place%20specified%20by%20the%20relatives%20of%20the%20deceased.%20But%20their%20work%20is%20not%20over%20with%20just%20digging%20graves.%20They%20are%20the%20last%20to%20leave%20after%20a%20deceased%20person%20has%20been%20buried%20as%20they%20have%20to%20fill%20the%20grave%20and%20level%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20no%20discrimination%20in%20Islam%20in%20terms%20of%20religion%20but%20there%20is%20segregation%20based%20on%20social%20status.%20For%20example%2C%20Ashraf%20are%20those%20who%20have%20land%2C%20property%20and%20prestige.%20They%20include%20Sheikh%2C%20Syed%2C%20Mughal%20and%20Pathan.%20The%20second%20are%20Azlaf%20which%20are%20communities%20offering%20various%20services%20such%20as%20carpenters%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebarhai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20barbers%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enaayi)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20tailors%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eidrisi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20dyers%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Erangrez%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20etc.%20One%20might%20equate%20them%20with%20the%20backward%20classes%20in%20the%20Indian%20constitutional%20system.%20There%20is%20no%20stigma%20of%20untouchability%20associated%20with%20these%20communities%20but%20the%20third%20category%20of%20Arzal%20communities%20is%20treated%20disparagingly%20even%20today.%20They%20include%20Lalbeggi%2C%20Halalkhor%20and%20Gorkan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Gorkan%20community%20are%20no%20longer%20there%20in%20Bihar%2C%20at%20least%20not%20according%20to%20the%20statistics%20in%20the%20survey.%20Does%20it%20mean%20the%20caste%20has%20become%20extinct%3F%20If%20yes%2C%20then%20who%20digs%20graves%20now%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20fact%20is%20that%20Gorkans%20are%20still%20there%20but%20the%20changing%20economy%20has%20forced%20them%20to%20switch%20professions.%20Earlier%2C%20the%20Gorkan%20community%20used%20to%20get%20religious%20protection%20and%20thrived%20on%20charity.%20As%20long%20as%20this%20system%20was%20in%20place%2C%20they%20stuck%20with%20their%20identity.%20But%20with%20time%2C%20this%20protection%20ended%20and%20other%20castes%20took%20over%20the%20task%20of%20digging%20graves%2C%20primarily%20the%20Nutt%20community.%20This%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20interesting%20castes%20of%20Bihar.%20They%20are%20both%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim.%20For%20example%2C%20at%20present%20in%20Bihar%2C%20the%20population%20of%20Hindu%20Nutts%20is%201%2C05%2C368%20and%20that%20of%20Muslim%20Nutts%20is%2061%2C629.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20difficult%20to%20say%20whether%20the%20people%20of%20Gorkan%20community%20have%20changed%20their%20caste%20after%20changing%20their%20profession%20like%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Nutt%20caste.%20But%20this%20possibility%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2